HOWEVER, MAPS WERE PRINTED IN VIENNA. ANOTHER STEP FORWARD WAS THE LIBERATION
FROM TURKISH RULE (1878), FOLLOWED BY THE FOUNDATION OF VARIOUS NATIONAL
INSTITUTIONS, HEADED BY THE STATE NATIONAL GEOGRAPHICAL INSTITUTE (1891) AND
THE UNIVERSITY OF SOFIA (1898) WITH THE CHAIR OF GEOGRAPHY . THERE WERE ALSO
HISTORIC MAPS PUBLISHED FROM 1878 TO 1944. AMONG THEM, THE MOST IMPORTANT IS
THE MAP OF UPRISING AND CLASS STRUGGLE, AIMING TOWARDS AND EVENTUALLY LEADING
TO THE LIBERATION AND UNIFICATION OF THE BULGARIAN NATION.
